  <description type="morphology">Leaves crisped and curled when dry, plane in many leaves, 2-stratose in distal 1/2, cells with longitudinal striolae in distal 1/2 of leaf; usually a few alar cells enlarged on margins, often colored.  Specialized asexual reproduction absent.  Capsule without differentiated annulus; peristome vertically striolate basally, weakly papillose distally.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Capsules mature spring–early summer.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Forming cushions on siliceous rock or gravel, occasionally epiphytic or epixylic;</description>
